INSERT INTO `wp_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES('2898', 'Greetings,\r\n\r\nWith the Affordable Care Act (ACA) in full effect, employers are searching for a wellness tool that makes a significant impact on improving employee health and reducing health care costs.\r\n\r\nSterling Wellness Solutions has an impressive array of wellness tools that provide disease maintenance and prevention. With healthcare expenses rising by 10-15%, the direction that companies are moving is disease reversal. \r\n\r\nOur company plays in the disease reversal arena and has over 25 years of evidence depicting our positive biometric and financial outcomes. These outcomes have been published in over 20 peer-reviewed medical journal articles. To view them, please click here. \r\n\r\nIf you would like to add one of the most efficacious and research-tested wellness tools on the market to your selection of wellness tools, then you should know about the Complete Health Improvement Program (CHIP). \r\n\r\nWhen running CHIP at Lee Memorial Health Systems in Ft. Myers, FL it realized the following outcomes:\r\n\r\n•        Avg. weight loss 17 pounds (26 total employees)\r\n•        Avg. BMI improvement 6.7 points\r\n•        Avg. cholesterol decline 27.7 points\r\n•        Savings of $4,000 per employee\r\n•        Net savings of $135,000\r\n\r\nI have seen great results from both community members and employees from all over the country. By implementing CHIP, employers can expect a 2:1 ROI.\r\n\r\nAlthough it was originally built as a community based program, it has recently been revised to be effective as a series of 18 one hour lunch and learns in a corporate setting. \r\n\r\nWhen working with employers, we have achieved the following outcomes: \r\n1.	Vanderbilt University employees (28 employees saved $75,000)\r\n2.	Lee Memorial Health System employees (26 employees saved $135,000)\r\n3.	Kaiser Permanente diabetic patients (42 patients reduced HA1c by an avg. of 1.9 points)\r\n4.	Christ Hospital employees (amazing change in culture and improved employee wellness)\r\n\r\nEach example showed very impressive results and is achievable in any organization. Recently, we got the University Of Pittsburg Medical Center on board and a commitment from Cummins Diesel in Indiana to run CHIP. We work in businesses with as few as 50 employees and as large as the aforementioned. \r\n \r\nI think CHIP would be a great addition to your corporate wellness package. Credible insurance agencies like Neace Lukens and partners of AssureX Global have researched the market and feel that CHIP is the best program of its kind. As such, they are recommending it to their clients.\r\n \r\nIf your wellness committee would like to vet CHIP, I would be happy to arrange a web conference to address what is CHIP, why CHIP works, and how organizations are using CHIP. \r\n \r\nLet me know your thoughts.\r\n \r\nKind regards,\r\n\r\nTravis Young\r\n909 283 6001');
